author: Ben Fox Rubin
title: Square publicly files for IPO
text:
Mobile-payments company Square disclosed Wednesday that it publicly filed for an initial public offering.
The move by the San Francisco-based company has been expected for months, with reports coming out over the summer that Square filed confidential paperwork with the Securities and Exchange Commission as part of its plans to go public.
This is a developing story.
